@@ -55,6 +55,10 @@ Active intelligence is stored at `/security/zenovguard-intelligence.zmid`; its m
 
 The active object is written before its version state. Boot reconciles a newer valid signed object with older version metadata, while an active object older than persistent state is rejected.
 
+Updates now retain the previous signed database in the existing supervisor-only scan workspace until the candidate passes a final-storage read-back, its version state is committed, the persistent `INTELLIGENCE-UPDATE` record succeeds, and ZenovFS metadata synchronization completes. The in-memory classifier is activated only after all of those gates. Any read-back, version, audit or sync failure restores the previous database and version and synchronizes the rollback; rollback failure leaves ZMID unavailable and the wider enforcement path fail-closed.
+
+This closes a prior split-brain state in which a signed candidate could remain persistent and active even though the audit append returned failure.
+
 ## Prevention boundary
